1. Download and install vagrant from https://www.vagrantup.com/
2. Install Oracle Java plugin for your browser
3. Add a Java security exception for 127.0.0.1:8080 
4. Create a directory and copy the files Vagrantfile and twister.sh into 
that directory; if you are behind a proxy server, edit twister.sh to
set the username, password and proxy server
5. Run 'vagrant up'
6. Once vagrant is up, open browser on host machine and go to
http://127.0.0.1:8080
7. Java security settings must be edited to add exception
 for http://127.0.0.1:8080 site
8. Connect to Twister with username 'user' and password 'password'
9. Select 'Test execution'
10. Ignore the warnings ( press OK )
11. Use the default project when you are prompted to select a project file
12. Now you have a project opened, to run press 'Run' button
13. To stop Twister virtual machine, run 'vagrant destroy'; Other options to
 stop the machine, please read vagrant documentation
